[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_5vwy8")
reagent_id = "H2O"
title = "Water"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]H₂O[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]18 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Liquid[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Colorless[/cell]
[cell]Smell:[/cell][cell]Odorless[/cell]
[cell]Boiling point:[/cell][cell]100 °C[/cell]
[cell]Freezing point:[/cell][cell]0 °C[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reaction[/b]
2H₂ + O₂ → 2H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Essential for all known life.
• A very good solvent (dissolves many substances).
• Exists in three states: ice (solid), water (liquid), and steam (gas).
• Has high heat capacity, helping regulate temperature on Earth.
[b]Where water is found[/b]
• In oceans, rivers, and lakes.
• In the atmosphere as water vapor.
• In living organisms.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Drinking and agriculture.
• Industrial processes.
• Cooling and heating systems.
• Chemical reactions.
[b]Safety[/b]
Water itself is safe, but polluted water can contain harmful substances or microorganisms.
"
